parameters: \n<Yurasa>We're getting close to the end now, I think!
\n<Yurasa>Yeah, I'm fine. Just like all the other fights we've gotten out of today.
\n<Elovia>I don't mean to come off as overbearing.\.\.\. I...
\n<Elovia>It's bad enough we're in this dangerous hellhole.
\n<Elovia>I want to keep you safe,\.\. but I worry that I've made some big mistakes.
\n<Yurasa>Hey, hey.\.\. Don't worry about me, alright?
\n<Yurasa>When we get back, pancakes'll be on me,\.\. 'kay?
\n<Elovia>\fiI wish I could be as sure as you, Yurasa.\fi
\n<Yurasa>I said\| if you die, do I get your stuff?
\n<Elovia>I swear, you care more about being funny than someone else's feelings.
\n<Elovia>Is everyone in the newer cities like you?
\n<Yurasa>And \fithat's\fi why I'm the funniest guy in the training grounds, hon.
\n<Yurasa>Alright then.\.\. If you're done being in awe of my acerbic wit, we've got an elevator to take.
\n<Elovia>...What was that look in his eyes?\.\. Did I imagine it?
\n<Yurasa>This is normal business for Gifted in the new cities, you know.
\n<Yurasa>In fact, it'd probably get buried as a footnote under some higher-class Hero's accomplishments.
\n<Yurasa>Look? See? Good as new.\.\. From gritty and ruggedly handsome back to my usual roguishly handsome.
\n<Elovia>(Stupid Elovia.\.\. Why did you treat him like a baby?)
